LivePerson Inc. (LPSN)  slid the most since
the shares listed in  Tel Aviv  in March after the customer-
service software maker issued a second-quarter outlook that was
below analystsâ€™ expectations.  The shares tumbled as much as 10 percent to 41.05 shekels.
They were down 5.8 percent at 10:45 a.m. in Tel Aviv  Second-quarter revenue will be $31.3 million to $31.8
million and adjusted earnings per share will be 6 cents to 8
cents, the company said yesterday in a PR Newswire statement.
Revenue was expected to reach $32 million and earnings 8 cents a
share, according to the median estimates of seven analysts on
